The majority of initial COVID-19 cases were associated with travel to Hubei Province, China; however, a growing number of cases due to person-to-person transmission have been reported both in and outside of China (Fig. 3
) [8,14,22,23]. Up to 94% of COVID-19 cases were reported to originate from Hubei Province in December 2019; as of March 2020, the greatest number of new cases are now being reported in Italy, Spain, Germany, and the United States (U.S.) (Fig. 3, Fig. 4
) [[24], [25], [26]].
